# Error Handling Flow

This diagram shows all 8 ProtocolError types and their handling paths through the Kernel.

## Error Classification and Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    start([Error Occurs]) --> classify{Error Classification}
    
    classify -->|Handle Validation| h1{Valid?}
    classify -->|Capability Check| c1{Permitted?}
    classify -->|Resource Check| r1{Available?}
    classify -->|Execution Phase| e1{Success?}
    
    h1 -->|No| eh[InvalidHandle]
    h1 -->|Yes| c1
    c1 -->|No| ec[PolicyViolation]
    c1 -->|Yes| r1
    r1 -->|No| er[ResourceExhausted]
    r1 -->|Yes| exec[Execute Action]
    exec -->|Timeout| et[Timeout]
    exec -->|Interrupted| ei[Interrupted]
    exec -->|Context Full| eco[ContextOverflow]
    exec -->|Parent Cancelled| eca[Cancelled]
    exec -->|Success| audit_ok[Write Audit: Ok]
    
    eh --> audit_eh[Audit: InvalidHandle]
    ec --> audit_ec[Audit: PolicyViolation]
    er --> audit_er[Audit: ResourceExhausted + Retry-After]
    et --> audit_et[Audit: Timeout]
    ei --> audit_ei[Audit: Interrupted + Token]
    eco --> audit_eco[Audit: ContextOverflow]
    eca --> audit_eca[Audit: Cancelled]
    
    subgraph integrity[Audit Integrity Check]
        check{Chain Valid?}
        check -->|No| eai[AuditIntegrityError]
    end
    
    eai --> audit_eai[Audit: IntegrityError + Alert]
    
    audit_ok --> return_ok[Return ActionResult]
    audit_eh & audit_ec & audit_er & audit_et & audit_ei & audit_eco & audit_eca & audit_eai --> return_err[Return ProtocolError]
    
